'''''The Bounty Hunter''''' is a "choose your own adventure"&ndash;style roleplaying book, written by [[Paul Cockburn]] and published, in the United Kingdom only, by [[Boxtree]] in [[1994]]. It was the second (and last) part of ''[[The Lost Jedi]]'' adventure game series. The story was later collected along with ''[[Jedi Dawn]]'' in ''[[The Lost Jedi Adventure Game Book]]''.

==Plot summary==
Two [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after his [[Jedi Dawn|first adventure]] on [[Toprawa/Legends|Toprawa]], [[Havet Storm]]&mdash;now a wanted man&mdash;attempts to leave the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], but finds himself once again involved in [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] affairs. Storm is on the run from the villainous [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] in an attempt to find and warn the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire's]] nefarious plans&mdash;before it's too late.

